Her paws twitched a little while she relaxed, tiny and smooth movements of 
her limbs letting Starice know that she was starting to fall asleep.
The baby was done eating and she moved her tiny mouth away from the end of 
the bottle, still half the milk left in it but her tummy was tiny like her 
body and full up already.
She made a squeek, her own little kind of burp. Her tummy, for the first 
time in a while, was round and full of warm milk.
Her little eyes started to close and then open again, close and open again 
until they closed for the last time and she fell into a very comfortable 
snooze. Half asleep but half awake too.
